The Supreme Court has upheld the elections of governors of Abia, Delta, Niger and Taraba states. A five-member panel of justices, on Wednesday, said Governor Okezie Ikpeazu (Abia State, PDP); Ifeanyi Okowa (Delta, PDP), Abubakar Sani Bello (Niger, APC); and Darius Ishaku (Taraba, PDP) were duly elected. Details later… Governorship: Results of 14 states set for tribunal Supreme Court judgments reduce tension — Sen Useni Mimiko is new chairman of PDP governors' forum